<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880126-0146 </DOCNO><HL> Unit of Unisys Wins $194.7 Million Order From U.S. Air Force </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UIS MD PKN GM </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sperry Corp., a unit of Unisys Corp., won a $194.7 million Air Force contract for an automated maintenance system.    Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. were issued contracts totaling $22.5 million to repair AH-64 helicopter equipment for the Army and to continue development of the T-45 pilot-training system for the Navy.    Avondale Industries Inc. received a $20.8 million Navy contract to overhaul a destroyer.    Perkin-Elmer Corp. was awarded a $19.9 million Navy contract for experiments to develop a directed-energy beam-control system.    Units of General Motors Corp. were given Navy contracts totaling $10.3 million for aircraft-engine parts and missile equipment.    (Revised WSJ Jan. 27, 1988)</TEXT></DOC>